@startuml
title Bank Service ERD (Immutable Ledger + Idempotency)

entity accounts {
  +account_id : varchar(128) <<PK>>
  bank_id : varchar(64)
  status : varchar(32)
  created_at : timestamptz
}

entity ledger_entries {
  +entry_id : bigint <<PK>>
  transaction_id : UUID
  account_id : varchar(128) <<FK>>
  operation_type : varchar(32)
  amount : decimal(18,2)
  direction : varchar(16)
  created_at : timestamptz
}

entity processed_operations {
  +transaction_id : UUID <<PK>>
  +operation_type : varchar(32) <<PK>>
  request_hash : varchar(256)
  result : varchar(32)
  processed_at : timestamptz
}

accounts ||--o{ ledger_entries : owns

note bottom of ledger_entries
Append-only records.
No update/delete in normal operation.
Balance is derived from entries.
end note

note bottom of processed_operations
PK(transaction_id, operation_type) enforces idempotency
for debit/credit/reverse operations.
end note

@enduml
